        <h2>Energy Efficiency and Savings</h2>
        <p>Modern combi boilers are significantly more energy efficient than older models, which can lead to substantial savings on your heating bills. If you're currently using a boiler that's 10-15 years old, upgrading to a new combi boiler could reduce your energy consumption by up to 30%, saving you hundreds of pounds per year on gas bills.</p>
        
        <p>All new combi boilers we install are A-rated for energy efficiency, achieving efficiency levels of 92-94%. This means that for every £1 you spend on gas, 92-94p is converted into useful heat for your home, with only 6-8p wasted. In contrast, old inefficient boilers may be only 60-70% efficient, wasting 30-40p of every pound spent on fuel.</p>
        
        <h3>Key Energy Efficiency Features:</h3>
        <ul>
