            <li><strong>Modulating Burners:</strong> Adjust flame size to match heating demand, reducing gas waste</li>
            <li><strong>Weather Compensation:</strong> Some models adjust output based on outside temperature</li>
            <li><strong>Smart Controls Compatible:</strong> Works with smart thermostats for optimized scheduling</li>
            <li><strong>Hot Water Priority:</strong> Ensures efficient hot water delivery on demand</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>The Energy Saving Trust estimates that replacing a G-rated boiler (less than 70% efficient) with a new A-rated condensing combi boiler could save you £315-£395 per year on average. Over the typical 10-15 year lifespan of a boiler, that's potentially £3,150 to £5,925 in savings. Combined with smart controls and proper system maintenance through annual servicing, you can maximize your energy savings and reduce your carbon footprint.</p>
