        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Combi Boilers</h2>
        
        <h3>How long does a combi boiler last?</h3>
        <p>With proper annual servicing and maintenance, a quality combi boiler should last 10-15 years. Premium brands like Worcester Bosch and Vaillant often exceed this, with some lasting 20+ years. Regular servicing is essential to maximize lifespan.</p>
        
        <h3>Can I shower while someone uses hot water elsewhere?</h3>
        <p>Modern combi boilers have improved hot water flow rates, but there can be a slight drop in pressure when multiple hot water outlets are used simultaneously. For homes with high simultaneous demand (multiple bathrooms in use at once), a system boiler might be more suitable.</p>
        
        <h3>Do combi boilers work with power showers?</h3>
        <p>Combi boilers provide mains pressure hot water, so you don't need a separate power shower pump. In fact, you cannot use a power shower with a combi boiler. The mains pressure is usually sufficient for a powerful shower experience with a modern thermostatic mixer valve.</p>
        
        <h3>What size hot water cylinder do I need to remove?</h3>
        <p>One of the great benefits of switching to a combi boiler is that you can remove your hot water cylinder completely, freeing up valuable space in your airing cupboard. You'll also be able to remove any cold water tanks from your loft. We handle all removal and disposal as part of our installation service.</p>
        
        <h3>Will I save money with a combi boiler?</h3>
        <p>Yes, if you're replacing an old inefficient boiler. New A-rated combi boilers are 92-94% efficient, compared to 60-70% for older models. This can save £300+ per year on gas bills. You'll also save money by not heating a full cylinder of hot water that you might not use.</p>
        
        <h3>How much does a combi boiler cost to run?</h3>
        <p>Running costs depend on your home size, insulation, and usage patterns. On average, a typical 3-bedroom home in the UK spends £700-£1,200 per year on gas for heating and hot water. A modern efficient combi boiler can reduce this by 20-30% compared to an old boiler.</p>
        
        <h3>Do I need to service my combi boiler every year?</h3>
        <p>Yes, annual servicing is essential and usually required to maintain your manufacturer warranty. An annual service costs from £80 and helps prevent breakdowns, maintains efficiency, ensures safety, and can identify minor issues before they become expensive problems. We offer <a href="/boiler-service-repairs/">annual service plans</a> for convenience and peace of mind.</p>
        
